South African techies plan to buy VW, BMW, and Ford cars in 2018, according to the MyBroadband 2017 Motoring Survey. The survey was completed by 1,356 tech-savvy readers, many of whom work in the ICT industry. 31.64% said they plan to buy a new car in 2018, with the majority aiming to spend between R300,000 to R500,000 on their purchase. Of those who plan to buy a new car, almost 10% expect to spend between R500,000-R750,000, while 3.73% said they will spend over R1 million. The results of the survey are detailed in the graphic below. 